7. A Simple Real Example

Let
	•	P = “I study”
	•	Q = “I pass the test”

Rule:

P → Q

If you study, you pass.

If you also know:

P

Then logically you conclude:

Q

This rule is called Modus Ponens, one of the fundamental inference rules.

